The paper discusses a method for acquiring data on hidden communities using online social networks (OSNs), which falls under the category of social informatics (cs.SI) and social computing (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the use of simulations, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CYBER) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of accurate statistical data for health interventions, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
